title: For Sale:  Antique Engraved .43 Mauser Sporting Rifle 1890s Near Mint Museum Piece
postcontent: For sale I have a beautiful Austrian made Sporting Rifle chambered in .43 Mauser. This Rifle was procured from a Museum in France that was closing their doors and once belonged to the Greatest Swiss Marksman and many beleive the greatest Target shooter to ever live Conrad Staheli. I acquired this Rifle along with his competition Rifle that he used to win gold in the 1900 Paris Olympics which is also listed for sale on this sight. This Rifle is a beautiful example of old world Craftmanship and is in incredible condition for its age. It retains nearly all of its original browned finish with traces of bright vivid case coloring in protected areas. One of the greatest and most innovative features of this Rifle is the rear tang sight that is built into the receiver hidden away from view to keep the very clean look of the rifle. It can be easily flipped up when needed then lowered so it becomes flush with the rear tang. Another great feature is the profusely engraved Horn Grip Cap that is engraved with the figure of Zeus King of the Gods. Along with that the Receiver, Trigger guard, and, underlever all have very tasteful engraved scroll  work. The Wood is near perfect with sharp checkering on both the buttstock and forearm and they both retain nearly all of their original varnish. The wood appears to be semi deluxe with a small amount of figure to it.  The top of the barrel has a beautiful checkering that was no doubt done by hand given the age of the rifle and is engraved with the makers name J. Rosler Salsburg who was listed as a Gunsmith to the Royal Austrian Court from the early 1880s to mid 1890s so you know his work was top notch. The bore is absolutely incredible and would rate a conservative 9 out of 10. All of this is contained in a very petite package weighing only 6 lbs. This is an incredible opportunity to own a beautiful museum quality piece from the old time Gunsmiths of the past. It is near impossible to get this type of quality today and if you do it will cost you Triple my asking price on this fine piece. This is considered and antique and as such can ship directly to your home. I will ship to the lower 48 for $40 insured. If shipping is required I would prefer payment by PayPal but will accept money orders, cashiers checks and personal checks with a 5 day clearing time. This Rifle is truly a Museum piece and sat in one in France for the last 60 years which would explain the incredible condition. Email, Call, or Text REDACTED. Many more pictures are available upon request.

title: For Sale:  1937 COLT 1911 1911A1 WWII British SOE OSS 1939 1941 1942 1943 1944 1945 US&S Commercial
postcontent: Selling an exceptional 1937 Colt 1911A1 Commercial British Proofed and in it's original Colt Brush Blue finish. I purchased this a while back from an estate of a long time collector who had this 40+ years. It is British proofed with the Broad Arrow and Crown over X1m stamp on the slide. I believe this to be a possible British SOE gun, basically their version of our OSS and were a direct action Commando unit(think Strike Back WWII). I had previously owned a Colt 1903 pocket model which had identical markings to this, and which the twin of appeared in Brunner's Colt Hammerless book 1. Those particular 1903's were a limited run sent directly to the SOE pre-WWII. This 1911 is marked near identical, however, the only way to be document it is to order a letter from Colt which I have not gotten around too. If you read about the SOE, they used a variety of weapons as guns were scarce pre-war. I may be mistaken and this could be just a regular Brit proofed pre-war Colt ordered pre-war, but the Broad Arrow stamp makes me think it is something special(again, near identical to the SOE 1903 I owned previously). The overall wear shows use and has some possible blood staining on the right side(very light pitting, can barely feel it with your finder nail). The pics show the rest, it is a fantastic Colt. Email with any questions before you bid. Thanks for looking and Happy New Year!
